# SIA P1 — Device-Actions LoRA Training (Google Colab Free T4)

This notebook fine-tunes a small LoRA adapter on the SIA device-actions dataset using Unsloth + TRL.

Runtime: **GPU** (free T4 is enough).

# Step 1 — Check GPU
!nvidia-smi

# Step 2 — Install deps
!pip install -q unsloth trl transformers datasets huggingface_hub

# Step 3 — Clone the SIA repo
import os
os.chdir('/content')
!rm -rf SIA
!git clone https://github.com/skmandal3240/SIA.git
os.chdir('SIA')

# Step 4 — Run the prepared training script
# Base model: unsloth/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct (Colab T4 friendly)
# LoRA r=16, alpha=16, 5 epochs, lr=2e-4, response-only loss
!python3 sia-lab/posttrain/sft.py --run --base unsloth/Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct --epochs 5

# Step 5 — Evaluate on the held-out validation set
!python3 sia-lab/posttrain/eval_adapter.py

# Step 6 — Merge and export to GGUF for Ollama
!python3 sia-lab/posttrain/merge_and_export.py

